This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the design of CTC-based all-neural speech recognizers, which involves the use of deep learning techniques for natural language processing. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel symbol inventory and iterated-CTC method, which are relevant to the field of computational linguistics. 

It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with speech recognition, which is a subfield of sound processing. 

Furthermore, it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of deep learning techniques for speech recognition. 

It could also belong to cs.SI (Signal Processing) as it deals with processing speech signals. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of neural networks for speech recognition.
